nter%20of%20a%20DOJ%20probe%20into%20the%20bank's%20Chair.%3Cp%3EHeather%20Diehl%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Federal%20Reserve's%20renovation%20project%20was%20expected%20to%20cost%20%241.9%20billion.%20It%20now%20has%20a%20%242.5%20billion%20price%20tag.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELead%20paint%20and%20asbestos%20discoveries%20contributed%20to%20increased%20renovation%20expenses%20and%20delays.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFed%20chairman%20Jerome%20Powell%20said%20a%20new%20DOJ%20probe%20is%20part%20of%20ongoing%20pressure%20from%20the%20Trump%20administration.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Federal%20Reserve's%20planned%20five-year%20renovation%20project%20is%20causing%20quite%20the%20stir%20in%20Washington.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERenovations%20began%20around%202022%20on%20two%20Federal%20Reserve%20offices%2C%20the%20Marriner%20S.%20Eccles%20Building%20and%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20East%20Building%2C%20which%20were%20first%20assembled%20in%20the%201930s%2C%20according%20to%20plans%20reviewed%20by%20the%20National%20Capital%20Planning%20Commission%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20workers%20gutted%20the%20aging%20structures%2C%20they%20uncovered%20lead%20paint%20and%20asbestos%2C%20pushing%20the%20cost%20of%20the%20renovations%20rose%20from%20%241.9%20billion%20to%20%242.5%20billion%2C%20as%20Federal%20Reserve%20chairman%20Jerome%20Powell%20described%20in%20a%20letter%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjerome-powell-defends-billion-federal-reserve-renovation-project-trump-inflation-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edefending%20the%20renovation's%20budget%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20year.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-jerome-powell-federal-reserve-renovation-interest-rate-inflation-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eblamed%20the%20overruns%20on%20mismanagement%20%3C%2Fa%3Eand%20allegations%20of%20luxury%20additions.%20On%20Sunday%2C%20Kevin%20Hassett%2C%20director%20of%20the%20administration's%20National%20Economic%20Council%2C%20told%20ABC's%20This%20Week%20that%20the%20project%20became%20%26quot%3Bthe%20most%20expensive%20project%20in%20D.C.%20history.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELater%20that%20day%2C%20Powell%20revealed%20the%20central%20bank%20now%20faces%20a%20potential%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomists-finance-business-leaders-react-trump-doj-investigation-fed-powell-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDepartment%20of%20Justice%20investigation%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20he's%20facing%20a%20potential%20criminal%20indictment%20over%20the%20cost%20increases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20one%20%E2%80%94%20certainly%20not%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20%E2%80%94%20is%20above%20the%20law%2C%26quot%3B%20Powell%20responded%20in%20a%20two-minute%20social%20media%20video.%20%26quot%3BBut%20this%20unprecedented%20action%20should%20be%20seen%20in%20the%20broader%20context%20of%20the%20administration's%20threats%20and%20ongoing%20pressure.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20questions%20swirl%20around%20the%20renovations%2C%20Business%20Insider%20gathered%20images%20of%20the%20construction%2C%20floor%20plans%20for%20the%20renovations%2C%20and%20design%20mock-ups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20Eccles%20and%20FRB-East%20buildings%20have%20been%20wrapped%20in%20scaffolding%20and%20cranes%20since%202022.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225441%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Scaffolding%20cranes%20tower%20over%20the%20Fed's%20building%20as%20scaffolding%20wraps%20around%20the%20office's%20exterior.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69652a05764ca5f34d2a46a0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223627%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Federal%20Reserve%20has%20been%20renovating%20its%20two%20buildings%20since%202022.%20The%20project%20is%20expected%20to%20wrap%20up%20by%20late%202027.%3Cp%3EHeather%20Diehl%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EConstruction%20workers%20broke%20ground%20on%20the%20renovations%20in%202022%20on%20the%2093-%20and%2088-year-old%20buildings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed%20said%20the%20building%20has%20not%20had%20a%20modernization%20project%20in%20decades.%20A%20series%20of%20decades-old%20electrical%2C%20heating%2C%20plumbing%2C%20and%20air%20ventilation%20systems%20ran%20through%20the%20historic%20building.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20project%20was%20necessary%20to%20%26quot%3Baddress%20a%20critical%20backlog%20of%20upgrades%2C%20to%20respond%20to%20changes%20in%20building%20codes%20and%20regulatory%20requirements%2C%20and%20to%20meet%20requirements%20for%20information%20technology%2C%20building%20security%2C%20environmental%20sustainability%2C%20and%20energy%20efficiency%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20plans%20produced%20by%20the%20Fed%20and%20released%20to%20the%20public%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EDocuments%20show%20the%20Fed's%20proposed%20floor%20plans%20for%20both%20buildings.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222618%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20floor%20plan%20of%20both%20Federal%20Reserve%20buildings%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6965362504eda4732f2ee913%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221324%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Federal%20Reserve's%20modernization%20plans%20were%20mapped%20out%20in%20an%20exhaustive%2087-page%20document%2C%20released%20in%202021.%20The%20document%20includes%20floor%20plans%2C%20mock-ups%2C%20and%20explanations%20of%20landscaping%20decisions.%3Cp%3EFederal%20Reserve%20Board%20and%20Fortus%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Federal%20Reserve%20published%20floor%20plans%20for%20the%20expansion%20project%20in%202021.%20The%20plans%20plot%20out%20details%20like%20where%20new%20windows%20would%20be%20erected%2C%20why%20new%20shrubbery%20would%20be%20planted%20in%20specific%20areas%20on%20the%20lawn%2C%20how%20it%20would%20make%20offices%20more%20wheelchair%20accessible%2C%20and%20where%20historic%20marble%20will%20be%20reused.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20release%20of%20the%20plans%2C%20construction%20workers%20have%20uncovered%20asbestos%20and%20lead%20paint%2C%20resulting%20in%20higher-than-expected%20material%20requirements.%20Inflation%20has%20also%20increased%20the%20price%20of%20those%20goods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EA%20mock-up%20of%20the%20exterior%2C%20including%20plans%20to%20add%20some%20glass%20structures.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222544%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20mock-up%20of%20the%20exterior%20of%20the%20Fed%20building.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69653625764ca5f34d2a4832%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221354%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Fed's%20renovation%20plans%20include%20new%20glasswork%20that%20will%20surround%20the%20historic%2C%20stone%20elements%20of%20the%20building.%3Cp%3EFederal%20Reserve%20Board%20and%20Fortus%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20modernization%20project%20would%20expand%20some%20sections%20of%20the%20Fed%20buildings%2C%20including%20areas%20with%20new%20glass-covered%20atriums.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20Eccles%20building's%20courtyard%20will%20be%20converted%20into%20an%20atrium.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222540%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20mock-up%20view%20from%20the%20second%20floor%20in%20the%20Eccles%20Atrium%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6965362504eda4732f2ee914%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221470%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20main%20building's%20atrium%20intended%20to%20mix%20%26quot%3Bhistorically%20significant%20spaces%20and%20work%20space%20to%20balance%20preservation%20and%20modern%20office%20needs.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EFederal%20Reserve%20Board%20and%20Fortus%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20courtyard%20at%20the%20center%20of%20the%20central%20bank's%20main%20building%20would%20become%20a%20glass-enclosed%20atrium.%20The%20renovation%20would%20also%20include%20new%20accessible%20ramps%2C%20and%20the%20existing%20wooden%20oak%20doors%20would%20be%20stained%20a%20medium%20brown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBoth%20historic%20buildings'%20interiors%20were%20finished%20with%20hand-carved%20wood%20in%20the%201930s.%20The%20woodwork%20will%20remain%20intact%20after%20the%20renovation.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222540%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Inside%20the%20renovated%20Eccles%20Building%20Level%204%20Lounge%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69653625764ca5f34d2a4830%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221420%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20renovation%20is%20supposed%20to%20keep%20historic%20architectural%20elements%20while%20updating%20the%20decades-old%20bones%20underneath.%20Here%20is%20an%20example%20of%20a%20fourth-floor%20lounge%20with%20the%20salvaged%20woodworking%20and%20marble%20floor.%3Cp%3EFederal%20Reserve%20Board%20and%20Fortus%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20the%20project%20is%20dedicated%20to%20balancing%20%26quot%3Bpreservation%20and%20modern%20office%20needs%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20plans.%20Several%20office%20spaces%20plan%20to%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ereuse%20marble%20and%20wood%20from%20the%20original%20buildings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20Eccles%20building's%20center%20wing%20skylight%20would%20be%20moved%20to%20the%20fourth%20floor%20to%20let%20the%20light%20stream%20in.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221892%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20peaked%20natural%20light%20shaft%20with%20bronze%20beams%20lets%20light%20strem%20into%20the%20fourth%20floor.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69653625764ca5f34d2a4831%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221176%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20natural%20light%20shaft%2C%20which%20was%20constructed%20in%201977%2C%20is%20also%20getting%20an%20update%20that%20the%20Fed%20says%20will%20introduce%20%26quot%3Bmore%20natural%20daylight%20to%20the%20historic%26quot%3B%20fourth%20floor.%3Cp%3EFederal%20Reserve%20Board%20and%20Fortus%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20natural%20light%20shaft%2C%20shown%20above%2C%20has%20sat%20on%20the%20top%20of%20the%20building%20since%201977.%20The%20renovation%20would%20relocate%20the%20glass%20casing%20to%20the%20fourth%20floor%2C%20allowing%20more%20light%20to%20enter%20nearby%20offices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20core%20architectural%20details%20of%20each%20building%20are%20important%20to%20preserve%2C%20the%20Fed%20said.%20It%20can%20help%20project%20financial%20power.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225616%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20statue%20of%20a%20bald%20eagle%20perched%20on%20top%20of%20the%20Eccles%20building.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F696540dd04eda4732f2eea33%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223744%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20project%20is%20meant%20to%20update%20the%20building's%20office%20capacity%20while%20maintaining%20its%20key%20architectural%20details%2C%20like%20the%20bald%20eagle%20perched%20atop%20the%20entrance.%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Harnik%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Eccles%20building%20was%20designed%20to%20project%20stability%20during%20the%20Great%20Depression%2C%20with%20marble%20halls%20and%20bronze%20fixtures%20meant%20to%20inspire%20public%20confidence%20in%20the%20banking%20system.%20Those%20original%20details%20are%20being%20carefully%20restored%2C%20the%20Fed%20said%20in%20the%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhite%20House%20officials%20have%20alleged%20the%20renovations%20include%20new%20VIP%20dining%20rooms%20and%20elevators%2C%20a%20vegetated%20roof%2C%20and%20millions%20of%20dollars%20in%20new%20marble.%20The%20Fed%20has%20denied%20those%20allegations%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalreserve.gov%2Ffaqs%2Fbuilding-project-faqs.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epress%20releases%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20Eccles%20building%20has%20been%20in%20disrepair%2C%20the%20Fed%20says.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ornate%20wood%20that%20was%20hand-crafted%20during%20the%20building's%20construction%20in%20the%201930s%20shows%20water%20damage%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F696572e9764ca5f34d2a4f45%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Fed's%20ornate%20architecture%20has%20endured%20nearly%20nine%20decades%20of%20wear%2C%20including%20water%20damage%20on%20the%20historic%20wood%20moldings%2C%20shown%20above.%3Cp%3EANDREW%20HARNIK%2FPOOL%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWater%20damage%20has%20been%20an%20issue%20for%20the%20historic%20buildings%2C%20according%20to%20images%20produced%20by%20Getty%20photographers%20in%20a%20July%202025%20walk-through%20of%20the%20construction.%20Pictures%20of%20the%20historic%20building's%20lobby%20show%20extensive%20damage%20to%20ornate%20wood%20carvings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAsbestos%20and%20lead%20paint%20have%20been%20a%20costly%20issue.%20Inflation%20hasn't%20helped%20either.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221738%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tarp%20is%20wrapped%20over%20sections%20of%20the%20Fed%20building%20where%20asbestos%20was%20found%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6965397164858d02d218304f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221164%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWorkers%20have%20been%20clearing%20asbestos%20from%20the%20building%20for%20much%20of%20the%20past%20decade.%20This%20picture%2C%20taken%20in%202017%2C%20shows%20a%20construction%20site%20inside%20the%20Eccles%20building%20where%20workers%20found%20the%20dangerous%20material.%3Cp%3EFederal%20Reserve%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed%20said%20it%20needed%20to%20make%20renovations%20to%20make%20its%20offices%20%26quot%3Bsafe%2C%20healthy%2C%20and%20effective%20places%20to%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%20plans.%20For%20years%2C%20workers%20have%20uncovered%20asbestos%20throughout%20the%20historic%20buildings%20%E2%80%94%20a%20material%20now%20banned%20in%20most%20construction%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20project%20continues%2C%20more%20materials%20have%20had%20to%20be%20replaced%20than%20expected.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frent-prices-steel-tariffs-apartment-development-increase-housing-costs-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EConstruction-sector%20inflation%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20made%20the%20overruns%20steeper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ETrump%20has%20seen%20the%20renovation%20project%20up%20close.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22President%20Donald%20Trump%20and%20Chair%20Jerome%20Powell%20toured%20the%20Fed%20building%20in%20July%202025.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69653fb804eda4732f2eea21%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22533%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%20and%20Federal%20Reserve%20chair%20Jerome%20Powell%20tour%20the%20Eccles%20building%20during%20the%20building's%20renovation.%3Cp%3EChip%20Somodevilla%2FGetty%20Images%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%202025%2C%20Trump%20toured%20the%20renovation%20project%20with%20Powell%20and%20Republican%20Sen.%20Tim%20Scott.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20a%20brief%20interview%20with%20reporters%2C%20Trump%20and%20Powell%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-jerome-powell-firing-fed-chair-interest-rates-inflation-bessent-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esparred%20over%20the%20cost%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20recent%20construction%20projects%20in%20the%20building.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20building%20is%20expected%20