Synchrony%20Financial%2C%20JPMorgan%2C%20and%20Citigroup.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20investors%20reacted%20to%20the%20latest%20threat%20to%20lenders'%20bottom%20line%2C%20UBS%20said%20that%20Trump's%20plan%20would%20have%20a%20negative%20impact%20on%20Main%20Street%20despite%20its%20intention%20to%20relieve%20high%20borrowing%20costs%20for%20many%20Americans.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUBS%20analyst%20Erika%20Najarian%20said%20that%20the%20proposed%20credit%20card%20rate%20cap%20would%20likely%20backfire%2C%20as%20it%20would%20likely%20reduce%20consumer%20spending%20and%20curtail%20lending%20to%20certain%20borrower%20groups.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENajarian%20said%20that%20credit%20card%20providers%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20dial%20back%20the%20availability%20of%20credit%20to%20certain%20borrowers%2C%20rather%20than%20simply%20offer%20cheaper%20credit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20pretty%20clear%20that%20a%2010%25%20credit%20card%20rate%20cap%20would%20cut%20off%20credit%20availability%20to%20those%20that%20need%20it%20most%3A%20middle-%20and%20lower-income%20Americans%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20of%20analysts%20at%20UBS%20said%20that%20while%20they%20see%20a%20low%20likelihood%20of%20the%20plan%20becoming%20law%2C%20the%20overall%20impact%20on%20credit%20availability%20would%20be%20felt%20by%20both%20investors%20and%20consumers.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAccording%20to%20the%20Boston%20Fed%2C%20the%20aggregate%20credit%20card%20spend%20by%20annual%20household%20income%20was%20as%20follows%20in%20May%20'25%3A%201)%20%26lt%3B%2439k%3A%20~%2426bn%3B%202)%20%2459-83k%3A%20~%2437bn%3B%203)%20%3E%24121k%3A%20%24175bn.%20Based%20on%20Boston%20Fed%20data%2C%20this%20means%2026%25%20of%20credit%20card%20spend%2C%20at%20least%2C%20would%20be%20at%20severe%20risk%2C%20implying%20a%20major%20impact%20on%20the%20economy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20analysts%20noted%20that%20consumer%20spending%20accounts%20for%20roughly%2070%25%20of%20US%20GDP%20on%20average.%20Additionally%2C%20credit%20card%20spending%20accounts%20for%20nearly%20half%20of%20Visa's%20payment%20volume%20and%20more%20than%20half%20of%20Mastercard's.%20The%20kind%20of%20pullback%20predicted%20by%20UBS%20could%20severely%20compromise%20US%20economic%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENajarian%20isn't%20the%20only%20finance%20pro%20to%20suggest%20that%20Trump's%20credit%20card%20rate%20cap%20plan%20could%20backfire.%20Billionaire%20investor%20Bill%20Ackman%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fackman-trump-call-cap-credit-card-interest-mistake-affordability-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edescribed%20it%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bmistake%26quot%3B%20and%20claimed%20that%20millions%20of%20credit%20cards%20could%20be%20cancelled%20as%20a%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-credit-cards-interest-rate-cap-backfire-ubs-cof-2026-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1768246204000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69654b7204eda4732f2eeb6b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-credit-cards-interest-rate-cap-backfire-ubs-cof-2026-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Trump%20called%20for%20interest%20on%20credit%20cards%20to%20be%20capped%20for%20a%20year.%20UBS%20thinks%20that%20would%20end%20up%20hurting%20credit%20availability%20for%20some%20borrowers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sobrient%40insider.com%20(Samuel%20O'Brient)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A40%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-credit-cards-interest-rate-cap-backfire-ubs-cof-2026-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mark%20Zuckerberg%20says%20Meta%20will%20build%20'hundreds%20of%20gigawatts'%20of%20AI%20capacity%20over%20time%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226864%5